  "text": "FGF2 mediates cell-cell attachment by linking FGFRs and HSPGs on neighboring cells through the formation of HSPG/ FGF2/FGFR ternary complexes. [CITATION_1] Indeed, HSPG-deficient FGFR1-transfected A745-CHO flg-1A cells adhere to a monolayer of HSPG-bearing CHO-K1 cells when incubated in the presence of 30 ng/mL FGF2 but not in the absence of the growth factor. 27 K5-N,OS(H) inhibits FGF2-mediated cell-cell attachment in this model. [CITATION_2] When tested under the same experimental conditions, all the LMW-K5 compounds and IMW-K5 hamper the formation of the HSPG/FGF2/FGFR ternary complex with an activity equal to that shown by the parent compound K5-N,OS(H) and LMWH (ID 50 ϭ0.3 g/mL) and only slightly less potent than that exerted by UFH (ID 50 ϭ0.1 g/mL). Unmodified K5 was ineffective (Figure 2A ).",
